deck: Collected reprints of true stories of African American achievement and bravery.

description:
In December 2015 the Tallest Tale yet from Jazan Wild's Carnival of Souls series was released for the Series 10th Anniversary. Look up and see... The Stilt Walker!

SYNOPSIS: Carnival of Souls: The Stilt Walker is the tale of Skyy, a Native American who rides high on the plains and who has all of his people looking up to him for his strength and courage. Able to see visions, one night a vision of two sets of wagons plagues his mind. One wagon carries pale face soldiers, while the other has a colorful crew and painted faced monster... known to the spirits as Jexter the Clown! Captured and hung out to dry in the scorching desert sun, Skyy just will not die. After all, he doesn’t know it yet, but he’s about to rise higher than ever before and become a Freak Show’s Warrior!
name: The Stilt Walker

description: When an escaped prisoner from Fort Rozz interrupts a football game, Supergirl is on the scene to take her down. But Rampage is mad about more important things than a sporting event-and no pesky superhero can stop her quest for revenge!
name: Chapter 1

description: Batman takes on Bane on the grounds of Wayne Manor, while Batgirl attempts to rescue Catwoman.
name: Chapter 6: Decoy

volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Five

description: With the addition of Chiyuri (Lime Bell), the Black Legion of Nega Nebulus now has four members. But when Kuroyukihime leaves the group to go on their school trip, her absence casts a pall over the friendship of Haruyuki, Takumu, and Chiyuri, threatening its very foundation. When Kuroyukihime returns to find Haruyuki cornered by the ruthless Dusk Taker, Haruyuki tells her everything! And with the appearance of Fuko Kurasaki--Sky Raker--the manga adaptation of Reki Kawahara's futuristic science-fiction novel series just keeps accelerating!
name: Touch The Window To Start "BB" Program

description:
It's Night Raid versus the Jaegers in Volume 5 of the hit dark fantasy Akame ga KILL!

When the Jaegers' Dr. Stylish attacks the Night Raid base, Tatsumi and the others are forced out of their hideout to escape the deadly assassin! But their predicament only worsens when word spreads that there are new enemies near the Capital...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 20: Kill the Intruders
  • Chapter 21: Kill the Mad Scientist
  • Chapter 22: Kill the Unexplored Territory
  • Chapter 23: Kill the Newbies
  • Akame ga Kill! Special Arc
name: Vol. 5

description:
The laboratory where corpses dance...

Stella remains locked in a life-or-death struggle with her brothers and sisters in order to keep her beloved brother Zeno alive. Dragged into a plot by fourth-eldest brother Maré, she now finds herself pitted against her second-eldest sister, Miser, who has awakened as the Queen of Corpses.

"Let's take these children who drank my 'blood'......and do a little experiment!"

Confronted with the walking dead, manipulated through Miser's blood, the irrepressible "Bloody Alice" makes her entrance and draws her gun--?!

Welcome to the haunted party thrown by poor little Miser.
name: Vol. 3

description:
With the coming of the next eclipse, Momiji discovers not only that the various trials may be quite different but that he may be more dependent on his classmates than he ever imagined. Still uncertain about how to properly wield his "character," can Momiji survive to face the next challenge much less graduation...?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 4: White
  • Chapter 5: Black
  • Chapter 5 Apocrypha: Banquet
  • Chapter 6: Water
name: Vol. 2

description: Another special side story installment! Life hasn't been easy on Oto Edogawa. Her family is in dire financial straits, she's ostracized at school, and now this—a strange phenomenon keeps happening at her home night after night...
name: Bonus Story 2

volume.name: Boys Over Flowers Season 2: Side Story

description: The horrifying experiment to make Accelerator into an all-powerful Level Six has commenced--and it involves the wholesale slaughter of the little sisters cloned from Mikoto Misaka. Can Touma find a way to stop the seemingly invincible Accelerator? Could it be that weakness is stronger than strength could ever be?
name: Vol. 4
